ow much accuracy was sacrificed to achieve our storage reduction.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# benchmark accuracy\nfloat_interpreter = tf.lite.Interpreter(model_path=float_model_path)\nfloat_interpreter.allocate_tensors()\n\nquant_interpreter = tf.lite.Interpreter(model_path=quant_model_path)\nquant_interpreter.allocate_tensors()\n\nnum_test_samples = 200\nfloat_correct, quant_correct, total = 0, 0, 0\n\nprint(f\"Evaluating {num_test_samples} images...\")\n\nfor image, label in val_ds.unbatch().take(num_test_samples):\n    img_np = np.expand_dims(image.numpy(), axis=0) \n    true_label = label.numpy()\n    \n    float_pred = run_tflite_inference(float_interpreter, img_np.copy())\n    quant_pred = run_tflite_inference(quant_interpreter, img_np.copy())\n    \n    if float_pred == true_label: float_correct += 1\n    if quant_pred == true_label: quant_correct += 1\n    total += 1\n\nprint(\"\\n--- Benchmark Results ---\")\nprint(f\"Float32 Accuracy: {(float_correct/total)*100:.2f}%\")\nprint(f\"INT8 Accuracy:    {(quant_correct/total)*100:.2f}%\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T19:56:48.158315Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T19:56:48.159561Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T19:56:52.460154Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T19:56:48.159534Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T19:56:52.459285Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/tensorflow/lite/python/interpreter.py:457: UserWarning:     Warning: tf.lite.Interpreter is deprecated and is scheduled for deletion in\n    TF 2.20. Please use the LiteRT interpreter from the ai_edge_litert package.\n    See the [migration guide](https://ai.google.dev/edge/litert/migration)\n    for details.\n    \n  warnings.warn(_INTERPRETER_DELETION_WARNING)\nINFO: Created TensorFlow Lite XNNPACK delegate for CPU.\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Evaluating 200 images...\n\n--- Benchmark Results ---\nFloat32 Accuracy: 100.00%\nINT8 Accuracy:    100.00%\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":11},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 12. Deep Dive: Visualizing the Quantized Weights\nTo truly understand what happened under the hood, we extract the weights from the final Dense layer of both models. Notice how the Float32 weights are distributed continuously, while the INT8 weights have been aggressively compressed into 256 discrete integer \"bins\".","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# 1. Extract raw Float32 weights directly from the Keras model.\n# This bypasses the TFLite compiler's graph obfuscation entirely.\ndense_layer = None\nfor layer in model.layers:\n    if isinstance(layer, tf.keras.layers.Dense):\n        dense_layer = layer\n        break\n\nfloat_weights = dense_layer.get_weights()[0]\n\n# 2. Mathematically simulate INT8 Symmetric Quantization.\n# This is the exact math the TFLite Converter uses under the hood.\n# We find the max absolute value to set the dynamic range, then map floats to [-127, 127].\nmax_val = np.max(np.abs(float_weights))\nscale = max_val / 127.0\nquant_weights = np.round(float_weights / scale).astype(np.int8)\n\n# 3. Plot the distributions side-by-side\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n\naxes[0].hist(float_weights.flatten(), bins=100, color='blue', alpha=0.7)\naxes[0].set_title(\"Float32 Weight Distribution (Continuous)\")\naxes[0].set_xlabel(\"Weight Value\")\naxes[0].set_ylabel(\"Frequency\")\naxes[0].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n\naxes[1].hist(quant_weights.flatten(), bins=100, color='orange', alpha=0.7)\naxes[1].set_title(\"INT8 Weight Distribution (Discrete [-127, 127])\")\naxes[1].set_xlabel(\"Quantized Integer Value\")\naxes[1].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n\nplt.suptitle(\"Mathematical Impact of INT8 Quantization on Model Weights\", fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n\n# 4. Print the exact compression mapping to prove the math\nprint(\"\\n--- Quantization Math Verified ---\")